Renames service-related constants and updates imports
Moves service constants to a dedicated services directory Updates import paths to use absolute references for easier navigation
Improves project structure and maintainability
refactor: enhance DynamicBreadcrumb component with improved rendering and styling
refactor: remove unused MaterialTailwind ThemeProvider from Providers component

feat: add FlyoutMenu and DynamicBreadcrumb components; update layout and providers
- Introduced FlyoutMenu component for navigation with mobile support. - Added DynamicBreadcrumb component for dynamic breadcrumb navigation based on the current path. - Updated RootLayout to include FlyoutMenu and DynamicBreadcrumb. - Modified Providers to wrap children with Material Tailwind ThemeProvider. - Implemented generateRandomString utility function for random string generation. - Created UI components for breadcrumb navigation including Breadcrumb, BreadcrumbList, BreadcrumbItem, and others.
Adds new dependencies for UI components and utilities

Updates path aliases for improved module organization
Refactors path aliases in configuration files to enhance clarity and maintainability.
Changes include updating the 'utils' and 'constants' paths to reflect their new locations in the 'lib' directory.
This restructuring aims to streamline imports across the project.

Removes unused font imports and integrates Providers
Eliminates unnecessary font imports to streamline code.
Introduces Providers component for improved layout management.
Enhances body structure for better responsiveness.

Adds NotFoundContextType interface
Implements a new type to manage not found states in the application.
This addition facilitates better handling of not found scenarios, allowing components to easily track and update their not found status.

Adds NotFound context and provider for error handling
Introduces NotFoundContext and NotFoundProvider to manage "not found" state within the application.
Wraps child components with NotFoundProvider in the Providers component to enable access to not found state throughout the app.
Improves overall user experience by allowing components to handle not found errors gracefully.

Adds service and tier information constants
Introduces structured data for various wellness services and tiers, enhancing the application's ability to provide detailed service offerings.
Supports better organization of service details, pricing, and session information for user access.
No related issues.

Enhances subServices with introductory descriptions
Adds optional introduction field to SubService interface Implements introductory descriptions for existing wellness programs Introduces new interfaces for subService and service tier information
Refactors ServiceCategory interface and adds SubService and SubServiceTier interfaces for enhanced service structure
Adds serviceCategories and subServices constants to define wellness, nutrition, fitness, mental health, and corporate wellness offerings
Adds ServiceCategory interface to define service category structure
Adds debounce utility function to delay function invocation
Adds utility functions for string manipulation and array filtering
Adds tw-animate-css dependency to enhance animation capabilities

Updates ESLint configuration to relax certain rules
Modifies ESLint settings to disable specific rules related to React hooks and TypeScript.
This change aims to reduce linting errors during development and improve code flexibility.
Relates to JIRA-456

Enhances TypeScript configuration for module resolution
Adds support for importing TypeScript extensions.
Expands path mappings to simplify imports across the project, allowing for clearer and more organized code structure.

Updates component aliases in configuration
Refactors component paths for better organization Changes 'utils' and 'ui' aliases to new locations Introduces 'constants' alias to enhance clarity
Relates to JIRA-456

Adds custom screen size detection hooks
Implements three custom hooks to determine screen sizes: - `useLargerScreen` for screens between 1025px and 1440px - `useMediumScreen` for screens less than or equal to 768px - `useSmallScreen` for screens less than or equal to 640px
Enhances responsive design capabilities by allowing components to adapt based on screen size.

Adds next-themes and react-icons dependencies
Includes next-themes for improved theme management in the application. Adds react-icons for enhanced icon usage throughout the UI.
No issues referenced.

Enhances color scheme and typography in styles
Introduces new color variables for improved theming Updates background and foreground colors for better contrast Adds custom fonts for enhanced visual appeal and readability
Relates to design improvements

Adds new font files for improved typography
Introduces several font files to enhance the visual appeal of the application.
Includes Barlow Condensed, Cormorant, DM Serif Display, IBMPlex Sans, Nunito, and Poppins fonts.
Improves overall design consistency and readability.

Adds new dependencies for UI components and updates
Introduces @headlessui/react and @heroicons/react for enhanced UI features. Updates tw-animate-css to the latest version for improved animations. Ensures compatibility with existing dependencies and enhances overall application functionality.
Relates to UI/UX improvements.

Updates navigation titles and descriptions for clarity
Renames "About Us" to "Our Story" for a more personal touch. Removes "FAQs" section to streamline navigation. Changes "Explore our range of flexible payment plans" to "Explore our range of services geared towards your every need" for better alignment with user expectations.

Removes obsolete contract and payment plan definitions
Deletes unused contract categories and payment plans to streamline the codebase and eliminate redundancy.
Improves maintainability by reducing unnecessary complexity.

Enhances ModeButton styling and accessibility
Improves visual appearance of the ModeButton component by adding background, border, and text color adjustments.
Updates accessibility features through improved aria-labels for better screen reader support.

Adds FlyoutMenu component and removes Navbar
Introduces a new FlyoutMenu component for improved navigation.
Removes the existing Navbar component to streamline codebase and enhance user experience.
Updates layout to include the FlyoutMenu in the main content area.
Improves responsiveness and accessibility in the navigation system.

Removes contract selection section from contact form
Eliminates the contract examples selection feature from the contact us page for a streamlined user experience.
Updates user interface by simplifying form fields and reducing complexity in the component structure.
